        <h2>How to Contribute</h2>
        
        <p>We welcome contributions from everyone! Whether you're a content creator, developer, or someone who's spotted a typo, your input helps make this site better.</p>

        <h3>For Content Managers</h3>
        
        <p>If you want to add or edit content using our Content Management System (CMS), we have a comprehensive guide just for you:</p>
        
        <p><strong><a href="https://github.com/your-org/uswds-starter-site/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">ðŸ“– Read the Complete Contributor Guide</a></strong></p>
        
        <p>This guide covers everything you need to know:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Getting access to the CMS</li>
          <li>Creating and editing content</li>
          <li>Working with images and formatting</li>
          <li>Publishing your changes</li>
          <li>Troubleshooting common issues</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For Developers</h3>
        
        <p>Technical contributions are also welcome! Here's how to get started:</p>

        <h4>Reporting Issues</h4>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/your-org/uswds-starter-site/issues/new">File an issue on GitHub</a> if you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Find a bug or error</li>
          <li>Have a feature suggestion</li>
          <li>Notice accessibility issues</li>
          <li>Want to propose improvements</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Submitting Pull Requests</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>Fork the repository</li>
          <li>Create a feature branch (<code>git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature</code>)</li>
          <li>Make your changes</li>
          <li>Test locally (<code>npm start</code>)</li>
          <li>Commit your changes (<code>git commit -m 'Add amazing feature'</code>)</li>
          <li>Push to your branch (<code>git push origin feature/amazing-feature</code>)</li>
          <li>Open a Pull Request</li>
        </ol>

        <h4>Development Guidelines</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Follow the existing code style and conventions</li>
          <li>Test your changes across different browsers</li>
          <li>Ensure accessibility standards are met (WCAG 2.1 AA)</li>
          <li>Update documentation as needed</li>
          <li>Keep commits atomic and well-described</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Questions or Need Help?</h3>
        
        <p>If you have questions about contributing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Check the <a href="https://github.com/your-org/uswds-starter-site/blob/main/README.md">README</a> for general information</li>
          <li>Review the <a href="https://github.com/your-org/uswds-starter-site/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">full contributor guide</a></li>
          <li>Open an issue to ask questions</li>
          <li>Contact your site administrator</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>
        
        <p>We are committed to providing a welcoming and inclusive environment. All contributors are expected to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Be respectful and considerate</li>
          <li>Welcome diverse perspectives and experiences</li>
          <li>Accept constructive criticism gracefully</li>
          <li>Focus on what is best for the community</li>
          <li>Show empathy towards other community members</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Recognition</h2>
        
        <p>All contributors will be recognized for their work. Your contributions help make government services more accessible and user-friendly for everyone.</p>
        
